the third secret : a novel of ( not that much ) suspense the third secret is another entry in the vatican intrigue genre . it has the usual elements : vatican conservatives the usual bad guys vs liberal catholics the usual good guys . the `` third secret '' refers to secret revelations given to marian visionaries at such places as fatima and medjugorge , the existence of which is historical fact . if there is any suspense in the novel , it is not with the plot which is remarkably predictable and derivative . the only thing that kept my interest was waiting to find out the actual content of the third secret ( s ) , at least according to the novel 's author . in the end , these proved to be rather predictable too , given the author 's religious inclinations